{"body": "@thefool808 theoretically one could over-ride the `nil?` or `is_a?` or any other method on an object, but that doesn't make it a good idea. If someone makes a column named `blank` or `present` in their database they will have more issues than just in this one method. In this situation i believe you can pass non AR objects such as an empty string \"\". That would not get caught by a simple nil check\n\nWe need to support this use case too:\n\n```\n<%= form_for :person do |f| %>\n```", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/8948393", "created_at": "2012-09-27T18:31:34Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7314#issuecomment-8948393", "updated_at": "2012-09-27T18:31:57Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7314, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/schneems", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/db953d125f5cc49756edb6149f1b813e?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F6ef42a6eab211ddd71ac423a80b42d15.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/received_events", "gravatar_id": "db953d125f5cc49756edb6149f1b813e", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "schneems", "type": "User", "id": 59744, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523df79bbd354364b900be7f"}, "id": 8948393, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7314"}
